    "description": "The strategy is a systematic signal follower that implements an externally generated daily model portfolio for US large cap equities. Each trading day is associated with a predefined list of long candidates and target portfolio weights (typically a concentrated basket of about five single name equities with weights summing near 100 percent), and the strategy seeks to harvest the alpha embedded in that upstream stock selection and weighting process rather than generating signals internally.\n\nOper",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a systematic signal follower that implements an externally generated daily model portfolio for US large cap equities. Each trading day is associated with a predefined list of long candidates and target portfolio weights (typically a concentrated basket of about five single name equities with weights summing near 100 percent), and the strategy seeks to harvest the alpha embedded in that upstream stock selection and weighting process rather than generating signals internally.\n\nOperations are end of day and fully rules based: once per day near the market close, if a signal exists for that date the portfolio is rebalanced to match the target weights. Positions not present in the current day list are fully liquidated, and positions in the list are initiated or resized to their specified fractional portfolio weights using current end of day pricing. If no signal is provided for a date or the signal is empty, the strategy takes no action and maintains existing holdings. Risk management is primarily via position sizing and concentration constraints implied by the input weights; there are no explicit stop losses, leverage limits beyond the weight budget, sector controls, or volatility targeting, so turnover and drawdown behavior are dominated by the external signal schedule and the concentration of the target basket.",
